*T-minus… oh… shoot… we started a minute ago…*

Thank you, everyone, for being here!

I started watching Lois & Clark in September 1993, the year it started airing—I was only 13 years old! Back in the day of VHS and dial-up internet and having to wait *all summer* to get the answer to Lois’s question at the end of season 2! I think I was 14 or 15 when I found the fandom online via the AOL chatroom and the LISTSERV (old-school word for newsletter/group email).
If you had told 14-year-old me where I’d be 30 years later … I would have probably written another “Crazy FoLC” story and assumed I was *actually* going crazy and HG Wells had found me. 😂

We had our first-ever Kerth Awards in 1998, just before I was to graduate high school. And would you believe that one of my first fics ever written got nominated for a Kerth? I was so thrilled and honored!

You know what it was for? For Best Wedding Story. Way-specific category, right? You know what else we had? Best Pregnancy/Delivery Story… because you’d better believe all the FoLCs back then NEEEDED something better than the series finale. 😭
We also had Best Revelation (Lois). Yeah, there were enough revelation stories to split them into just Lois finding out that ||Clark Kent is Superman|| and another for everyone else finding out!

There was also Best Music/Poem Adaptation *AND* Best Poem. Best Lex Story, anyone? Best Tempus Sto— 

*gets a nudge and whisper from Michael…*

Okay well, @Darth_Michael says that I’m “giving grandpa telling old stories for eons vibes” and that I should wrap it up because the ceremony will already be hours long. And as most FoLCs can tell you, I have a tendency to ramble, especially with my author’s notes and—
*gets a firmer nudge and a whisper-yell from Michael*
Um, yep! Wrapping up!

FoLCdom has given me SO much over the past three *decades*, that I’m really *super* honored to be here hosting the Kerth Awards, and I’m so grateful that the fandom is still going after all these years!  So without further ado—
*glares at a laughing Michael*
Just so you know, I’d be done if you hadn’t interrupted!

So without further ado or *interruption*…  
I’d like to bring up @AnnaBtG to present our first award!
Hello hello and welcome to the Kerths!
I’m not going to wax poetic, because our first category is **Best Micro-Short**! So in honour of these wonderful authors who kept it micro-short and sweet, here are our nominees in a nutshell:

- **A Chance Meeting in A Parking Lot by Queen of the Capes**, in which Clark finds himself running into a Lois whose behaviour is… a bit peculiar.
- **The Cold Treehouse by SuperBek**, in which Clark reminisces about a place that’s very special to him.
- **Dessert by 90stvfangirl**, in which Lois looks pretty darn fit!
- **Krypto Meets A New Friend by Morgana**, which answers the age-old question of whether cats and dogs can get along.
- **The Ring by Toomi8**, a story about Clark’s ring from Honeymoon in Metropolis.
- **The Story I've Never Seen by Shallowford**, in which the events in the end of And The Answer Is take a literal turn.
- **Walk The Dog Challenge 4: A Walk In The Park by bakasi**, another story featuring Krypto and his shenanigans!
And the winner is…

We’ve had a couple of new FoLCs in the past few months, which is absolutely awesome. One of the first questions asked when adapting to this wonderful fandom is
What does WAFFY mean?
It’s an acronym for Warm and Fuzzy Feeling.
It’s like a bite of chocolate (if you enjoy chocolate that is) without the calories.
It’s like a cup of hot apple juice with cinnamon that’s delicious regardless of the season.
It’s like a hug in print.
It’s the type of story that leaves you with a general sense of well-being after a rough day.
I guess we all have our favorite go-to stories, when we’re feeling down. Stories that cheer us up, even if they might not be particularly funny. And they come in all sizes and packages.

**110 Kisses: You Made Your Choice** by KSaraSara has Lois regret her decision to turn Clark down when he confessed his love. There’s heartbreak right there - but also hope - because she tells him how she really feels

**2023 Ficathon: Christmas Lights for KSaraSara** by JadedEvie  has Lois in dire-straits. The Prankster is after her and tries to show her how isolated she is in this world. But then Clark comes to her rescue – in both his guises. And it takes his true superpower to save her - his big heart.

**2023 Ficathon: Planes, Trains and Deep Fried Mars Bars for Queen of the Capes** by lovetvfan takes us on an amazing trip to Scotland where our favorite couple ends up by accident. But they discover so much more than they were looking for. Deep Fried Mars bars, and each other.

**Falling For a Farm Boy** by Female Hawk  tells us the story of a different Lois and Clark, both struggling in their respective lives. Lois with the mistake she made and Clark with grief after his father died. And while they wait for a little calf to be born, they’re slowly falling in love.
It’s magic like this that never gets old.
So this year’s award for the **Best Waffy story** goes to…

Imagine a universe where fans only ever read the original episode scripts, posting and sharing them completely unchanged.  In this world, there are no what-ifs, no alternate endings or roads not taken, no original characters or new plots of any sort: only the canon, static and pure.  Sounds dull, doesn't it?

Writing a story requires imagination.  Every piece of fanfiction we enjoy exists because someone chose to unleash their own creativity rather than passively accept what's already been shown in canon.  And every once in a while, someone dares to let their imagination go completely wild, remaking the very foundations of the story into something new and unfamiliar and exciting!

Welcome to Elseworlds and AUs, where nothing about the canon can be taken for granted.  Here, Lois and Clark are living very different lives before the story even begins.  Those lives may involve a Kansas farm, or an alien ghetto, or an unexplained ship.  But while anything is possible, one thing is certain: you'll be just as curious about the beginning of the story as you are about the end.
The nominees for **Best Elseworlds/AU Story** are:

- **District K: Injustice** by AmandaK
- **Falling For a Farm Boy** by Female Hawk
- **Lois and The Spaceship** by 90stvfangirl

Ah, yes, I was supposed to talk about our fan sites today.
I guess most of you have already heard the news earlier this year but…
**Our servers are now hosting not just the message boards and the nfic archive and the Kerth site, but also the official Lois & Clark Fanfiction Archive!**

Lauren has maintained the Archive out of her own pocket for more than 30 years and all on her own time, but with her current webhoster becoming more and more unreliable, we decided to merge our efforts.
Luckily for us, our server has enough capacity to take on the extra load.
And I can tell you now, Lauren was more than excited about how the migration turned out and how well the Archive is running on our shared server now!
So, what does that mean for regular FoLC?
Well, nothing really, except that the pages load a bit snappier.

What’s more important is that Sara and Bek are now able to really spin up their work as Co-Editors in Chief of the Archive and will work hard to get Archive contributions up and running and processed into the Archive, now that Kerth season is over and there’s supposedly time for other things.

On the technical side of things, I also got a couple of plans to bring our FoLC sites into the next decade and reduce the burden of maintaining the Archive by reducing the manual labor required to add a story to the Archive.
There will be more announcements as things progress!

The next payment will be in early 2027 and we need to collect the funds for this payment over the next year and a half.
**At present, this goal is still about 800 USD away.**
Now, there’s two ways to tackle this:
One is to consider we got about 20 hardcore FoLCs and if everyone chips in 20 bucks a year, we’re all set!

Hi everyone! 
 
I’m SuperBek, last year’s winner of Best New Author, and I’m here (or…not 😅) to present this year’s award for Best New Author!
It’s really amazing to me that even after 30+ years, the fandom is still continuing to add new authors every year, and I truly think part of that is because of how welcoming the community is.

When I came back to writing after a long, long break, I had so many stories in my head just bursting to come out. I wrote and wrote and wrote (mostly long, angsty stories that put Clark through the wringer a bit 😅). Because of a bad experience I’d had when I was younger, I was *terrified* to share my work (I’m talking seriously severe anxiety here!), and when I *finally* worked up the courage to post my first story (after reaching out to KSaraSara), I was blown away by how supportive the community was. **Seriously, y’all are amazing.**
It’s thanks to you all—your encouragement, feedback, and gentle (or not) prodding—that I became confident enough to write more and share more…even when the story, uh, wasn’t *exactly* canon. 😂😎😏
And I think the encouraging, welcoming community here is the main reason the fandom is still seeing an influx of new authors every year, even so long after the show ended.
This year, we have __four authors__ nominated for Best New Author! Each of these authors finished posting or sharing their first L&C fic in 2024!

So, without further ado, the nominees for **Best New Author** are:
 
- **AmandaK**
- **Aurore**
- **CalliopeWayne**
- **drdeathdefying**
